{{Quote|To set foot in the tomb of Naga Sadow is to breathe in death itself.|[[Darth Baras]]|<ref name="Star Wars: The Old Republic">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]''</ref>}}
The '''Tomb of Naga Sadow''' was a [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] tomb that was built at the behest of the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Tulak Hord]] in the [[Valley of the Dark Lords/Legends|Valley of the Dark Lords]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]]. Centuries later, it was to be the tomb of the reigning [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]], [[Naga Sadow/Legends|Naga Sadow]], but the [[Great Hyperspace War/Legends|Great Hyperspace War]] saw the collapse of the [[Sith Empire/Legends|Sith Empire]], and Sadow [[Death/Legends|died]] on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]]. Nonetheless, the structure remained known as the Tomb of Naga Sadow.

==History==
{{Quote|So explain this to me. The tomb of Naga Sadow on Korriban was built by Tulak Hord before Naga Sadow was even born?|[[Talos Drellik]]|<ref name="Star Wars: The Old Republic" />}}
The tomb was built for [[Naga Sadow/Legends|Naga Sadow]] in the [[Valley of the Dark Lords/Legends|Valley of the Dark Lords]], though he never occupied it, as the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] spent his remaining years in exile on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]].
It housed an ancient [[Rakata/Legends|Rakatan]] [[Star Map]] built when the Infinite Empire conquered Korriban.
During the [[Jedi Civil War]], the nearby [[Sith Academy (Korriban)|Sith Academy]] used the tomb as a final testing ground for their students.
[[File:Opening_the_door.png|thumb|left|[[Darth Nox|Kallig]] releasing [[Khem Val]]]]

[[Revan/Legends|Revan]] entered this tomb twice; once when he was on his journey to find the [[Star Forge]], but on his second visit&mdash;when he had his mind wiped by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]&mdash;he [[Skirmish on Korriban|confronted]] and killed the Sith Academy's leader, [[Uthar Wynn]], and redeemed [[Yuthura Ban]], Wynn's [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentice]]. In [[3951 BBY]], the Jedi Exile [[Meetra Surik]] tried to enter the tomb, but was unable to get inside, as the entrance was blocked by a rockfall. The tomb housed two [[Terentatek/Legends|terentateks]], a few [[wraid]]s, and the remains of [[Shaela Nuur]].

There were also many items that Revan found there, including Sadow's [[Naga Sadow's poison blade|poisoned sword]], a fire and ice grenade, and a ceremonial [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]]&mdash;which Revan was required to find as part of the final test.

[[File:Ancient_Droid_Guardian.png|thumb|Ancient droid guardian]]
During the [[Great Galactic War]], the [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|Sith]] retook [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]] and by the time of the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]], both Imperials and Sith thrived in the valley. The tomb was guarded by several ancient droids. Many [[Sith acolyte/Legends|Sith acolytes]] went there to complete several tasks assigned by their [[Overseer (Sith)|overseers]]. Overseer [[Harkun]] sent a promising [[Darth Nox|acolyte]] there to retrieve an ancient map for [[Darth Zash|Lord Zash]]. However, first the acolyte had to release, by gathering ancient rods, the ancient servant of [[Tulak Hord]], an infamous [[Dashade/Legends|Dashade]] called [[Khem Val]], who was also imprisoned in the tomb. When the acolyte released him, after killing countless other rival acolytes, the Dashade attacked the acolyte, enraged, after hearing that his master, Tulak Hord, had died hundreds of years earlier. However, he was defeated and so promised to serve the young [[Sith Order|Sith]]. They then [[Mission to Naga Sadow's tomb|retrieved]] the map, but first had to defeat an ancient guardian beast, a Terentatek Mauler. Later on, a promising [[Empire's Wrath|warrior]] was sent by [[Darth Baras|Lord Baras]] to the tomb to retrieve an ancient lightsaber. There, using the help of a [[Vette|Twi'lek prisoner]], he opened a secret chamber inside the tomb, terminated Naga Sadow's ancient droid guardians, and retrieved the lightsaber from his "grave".

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|It smells like death here. Not good, honest, battlefield death... but a musty, wasting death.|[[Canderous Ordo]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref>}}
A glitch can occur when in the terentatek room. If the player pulls the lever and runs into the room with the fire and ice grenades before defeating the terentateks, they cannot be followed by them. They can then attack them without fear of being attacked themselves.

[[Rakata/Legends|Rakatan]]-style monuments can be found in a couple of the rooms, such as the obelisk as monument to Naga Sadow and the stones which contained the special grenades.

This tomb appears also in ''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]] (MMORPG) by [[BioWare]] released on [[December 20]], [[2011]].

